The examination of how PLEs influence the attainment of SDGs was conducted through the application of the concepts of synergy and trade-offs. Positive correlations, exemplified by instances where increases in subsets of PLEs-LUT or PLEs-LF contributed to the advancement of SDGs, were indicative of synergy. In contrast, negative correlations, where increases in subsets of PLEs-LUT or PLEs-LF impeded progress toward SDGs, signified trade-offs. These relationships were quantified employing the nonparametric Spearman rank correlation coefficient (

